title: Middle States Intercollegiate Football League
text:
The Middle States Intercollegiate Football League (MSIFL) was an early <a href="College%20athletics">intercollegiate athletic</a> <a href="college%20football">football</a> conference which played for the 1893 and 1894 seasons.
Member Schools.
The members who made up the MSIFL were <a href="Lafayette%20College">Lafayette College</a>, <a href="Rutgers%20University">Rutgers College</a> (now <a href="Rutgers%20University%E2%80%93New%20Brunswick">Rutgers University–New Brunswick</a>) and <a href="Stevens%20Institute%20of%20Technology">Stevens College</a> (now <a href="Stevens%20Institute%20of%20Technology">Stevens Institute of Technology</a>).
